I'm not crying, you're crying! Operation Prom Surprise is complete as roses were delivered to 121 Duxbury Junior girls on their (supposed-to-be) Prom Night. Shout out to the DHS Student Council, and teachers Kate Bonneau, Stacey O'Brien, and Maria Dow for making great memories. Their focus was to spread joy and positivity during a very challenging time, and boy, did they ever!

Also many thanks to Kingston Florist for their generous donation of 150 roses 👍

post_text: As you may have noticed, we are removing several trees along St. George St. The tree work was approved at Town Meeting after two independent arborists concluded they were rotting and dangerous. No one likes to remove trees, but it had become a safety hazard. I wanted to share these pictures with you to illustrate the level of decay we were dealing with - our students walked under this particular tree every day!
